    <h1>2.1 Using Soul XML Libraries</h1>

    <h2>2.1.1 Creating a Project</h2>

    <p>
        To create a project that uses the Soul XML library components:
    </p>

    <ul>
        <li>Create a Soul-compatible project as described in <a href="../../tutorial/lexer/project.html">this</a> document.</li>
        <li>
            Right-click the solution in the Solution Explorer and select 'Add | Existing Project...'
        </li>
        <li>
            Navigate to the <span class="mono">C:\soul-4.0.0\soul\ast</span> folder and add the <span class="mono">ast.vcxproj</span> to the solution.
        </li>
        <li>
            Do the same for
            <ul>
                <li><span class="mono">C:\soul-4.0.0\soul\common</span>,</li>
                <li><span class="mono">C:\soul-4.0.0\soul\lex</span>,</li>
                <li><span class="mono">C:\soul-4.0.0\soul\lexer</span>,</li>
                <li><span class="mono">C:\soul-4.0.0\soul\parser</span>,</li>
                <li><span class="mono">C:\soul-4.0.0\soul\token</span>,</li>
                <li><span class="mono">C:\soul-4.0.0\util</span>,</li>
                <li><span class="mono">C:\soul-4.0.0\soul\xml\dom</span>,</li>
                <li><span class="mono">C:\soul-4.0.0\soul\xml\dom_parser</span>,</li>
                <li><span class="mono">C:\soul-4.0.0\soul\xml\processor</span>,</li>
                <li><span class="mono">C:\soul-4.0.0\soul\xml\xml_parser</span> and</li>
                <li><span class="mono">C:\soul-4.0.0\soul\xml\xpath</span></li>
            </ul> projects.
        </li>
    </ul>

